	<text>
		<body>
				<p><placeName>Memphis</placeName> <date>April 5619</date></p>
				<p rend="align(center)">Dear &#38; Rev Sir&#33;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Your favor came duly to hand.  I am very obliged to you<lb/> for the various hints you gave me and will endeavor to profit by them<lb/> <sic>Inclosed</sic> four <sic>dollar</sic> for the two prayer books.  I have<lb/> found here by a gentleman <persName>Mr. Kaufman</persName> two of your bibles<lb/> which you sent him some years ago&#44; it is true they do not look<lb/> any more new but still&#44; they can be used&#44; send me an order that<lb/> he can deliver them to me and I will endeavor to get you money<lb/> for them&#44; they are worth I suppose from 3 till 4 dollars yet.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I have also commission upon one of the <sic>larg</sic> bibles which you are<lb/> now publishing&#8212;please send me <del>also</del> one copy <persName>Schwarz</persName>&#44; Geography of <placeName>Palestine</placeName><lb/> and state me the price&#44; also two other <add>Hebrew</add>&#44; though they are not yet<lb/> ordered to me.  I have lectured again before the <sic>litterary</sic> society<lb/> subject &#8222;Temperance among the Israelites&#8221; if you wish to publish<lb/> it&#44; give me a hint of it in the &#8222;Occident&#8221; under notice to correspondence</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">The reason that we can for the present do not a great deal for<lb/> the <sic>occident</sic> is because many have still <hi rend="underline">the Israelite</hi>&#44; and <hi rend="underline">two</hi> of<lb/> course are too much&#33; yes the condition of the Israelites in the country<lb/> is still worse than is the large cities&#44; the bread we eat is <add>Hebrew</add>.<lb/>  <sic>for</sic> one thing&#44; it is <sic>sory</sic> we must confess it&#44; are the reformers better&#44;<lb/> they support their ministers better&#44; are more polite.</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Yours in faith</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)"><persName role="author">Jacob Peres</persName></p>
				<p>P.S. Do you not <sic>intent</sic> to finish <persName>I. S. Reggio</persName>.  I wish you would&#44; as I intend<lb/> to have it published as a whole&#44; by your aid.</p>
		</body>
